        "title": "Text 21",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Sofia&#x27;s Strategy</strong></p><p>Sofia is scaling the ratios.</p><p>Sofia seems to be using multiples of 6 and 48. Using this strategy, she has &quot;missed&quot; $104, and she will &quot;miss&quot; the 20 boxes.</p><p>         6 boxes for $48</p><p>         12 boxes for $96, and</p><p>         18 boxes for $144</p><p>         24 boxes for $192</p><p>Sofia may want to use common factors to scale the ratio to smaller amounts of each quantitiy. Finding the cost for 1 box would make it easy to scale up using different multiples. </p>"
          ]
        }
